#######################################
#            Cusp v0.6.1              #
#######################################

Summary
  Cusp v0.6.1 modernizes the codebase for CUDA 12+ and CCCL (formerly Thrust).
  This release removes deprecated C++ constructs, updates the build system, and
  adds GitHub Actions CI with code coverage.

New Features
  GitHub Actions CI with OpenMP and TBB backends
  Code coverage reporting via Codecov
  SCons-based build system for tests and examples

Breaking API changes
  Removed deprecated std::unary_function and std::binary_function usage
  Replaced cudaThreadSynchronize with cudaDeviceSynchronize throughout
  Requires CCCL (CUDA C++ Core Libraries) instead of standalone Thrust

Bug Fixes
  Fixed -O3 optimization issue with dangling T&& references
  Fixed out-of-bounds memory error
  Fixed type compatibility issues with C++12 and later standards
  Fixed csr_vector to use correct dispatch detail
  Fixed join_iterator constant_tuple definition for modern compilers
  Fixed identity operator to use std::identity
  Updated cusparse calls to newer cusparseSpGEMM routine
  Used _CCCL_HOST_DEVICE and fully qualified ::cuda:: namespaces throughout
  Added SM 9.0 support

#######################################
#            Cusp v0.6.0              #
#######################################

Summary
  Cusp v0.6.0 provides support for CUDA 8.0 and CUDA 9.0 with Thrust 1.8+.
  This release reflects a major refactoring of the execution policy dispatch
  system across all algorithms, closer integration with Thrust's internal
  execution policy structure, and substantial improvements to BLAS integration,
  the smoothed aggregation AMG solver, and complex type support.

New Features
  Generalized SpGEMM with user-defined initialize, combine, and reduce operations
  Block CSR SpMV for multiple right-hand-side vectors
  Refactored BLAS routines with CUBLAS and CBLAS backend integration (levels 1-3)
  Policy-based execution dispatch for all algorithms including multiply, transpose,
    elementwise, convert, sort, graph, and krylov solvers
  Policy-based LAPACK interface
  Refactored smoothed aggregation AMG with policy-based dispatch for all components
    including strength, aggregation, smooth_prolongator, and hierarchy extension
  Custom AMG example demonstrating user-defined SA dispatching
  Generalized monitor and linear_operator classes to use execution policies
  Optimized CSR MatrixMarket reader (resolves #66)
  Improved support for complex types in SA, printing, random values, and testing
  Grapple profiler implementation with timing support
  Evolution strength of connection measure for SA
  CUB-based COO and CSR SpMV kernels
  Custom binary function support in DIA and COO SpMV kernels
  MSVC and Clang compiler support improvements

  Algorithms
    cusp::multiply with generalized SpGEMM
    cusp::blas level 2 and level 3 routines (GEMM, GEMV, TRMV, etc.)

Bug Fixes
  Fixed shared memory error in blocked CSR SpMV
  Fixed logical error in valid entry counts for coo_matrix conversions
  Fixed CUDA 9 build errors and imported thrust launch routines
  Fixed errors in lobpcg and lanczos solvers
  Fixed MIS aggregation errors across multiple dispatch paths
  Fixed cross-system copy and conversion path errors
  Fixed OpenMP elementwise, SpGEMM, and matrix-matrix multiply errors
  Fixed dispatching errors in OMP backend and sequential conversions
  Fixed CUBLAS and CBLAS interface routines for complex types
  Fixed LAPACK stev template error
  Fixed BFS to support unsymmetric matrices and long long types
  Fixed missing conjugate in GMRES plane rotation
  Fixed row indexing bug in COO SpMV
  Fixed temporary_array errors in sequential csr_block_spmv and SA
  Fixed permutation_matrix template parameters and multiply
  Fixed coo_matrix_view indices initialization and conversions
  Resolved issues related to Thrust 1.7.0, 1.7.2, 1.8.0, and 1.8.3
  Resolved issues related to MSVC, GCC 4.4, and Clang
  Disabled two-phase BFS expansion (resolves #72)

#######################################
#            Cusp v0.5.1              #
#######################################

Bug Fixes
  Fixed coo_matrix_view conversion error
  Fixed interface error in LAPACK routines
  Fixed memory access error in counting_sort
  Fixed memory access error in DIA generalized_spmv
  Fixed smoothed_aggregation and polynomial smoother errors related to VS2013
  Added cusp/blas.h for compatibility with v0.4.0
  Added convergence, default and verbose monitors for compatibility with v0.4.0
  Added missing header files for size_t defs
  Updated multiply interface for tighter integration with policy-based dispatching

#######################################
#            Cusp v0.5.0              #
#######################################

Summary
  Cusp v0.5.0 provides support for CUDA 7.0RC and Thrust 1.8. This release
  reflects a major refactoring of the dispatch system and provides closer
  integration with the internal structure of Thrust. This release also
  marks a substantial improvement in the overall documentation of Cusp.

New Features
  Gauss-Seidel and SOR relaxation methods for CSR matrices
  Implementation of robust Lanczos and LOBPCG eigensolvers (experimental)
  Native implementation of BFS, imported from back40computing
  Policy based interface to control execution and memory allocation of algorithms
  Support for generalized SpMV operations on any sparse matrix
  Unified verbose_monitor and convergence_monitor functionality into the default monitor class
  New IO routines to read graphs or matrices stored in DIMACS or binary format
  counting_sort implementation to improve the performance of host sorting routines
  join_iterator used to combine separate iterators in an arbitrary order
  random_iterator used to generate random numbers

  Algorithms
     cusp::graph::vertex_coloring
     cusp::relaxation::gauss_seidel
     cusp::relaxation::sor
     cusp::relaxation::jacobi
     cusp::io::dimacs
     cusp::io::binary

Bug Fixes
  Resolved issues related to Thrust 1.7 & Thrust 1.8
  Resolved issues related to CUDA 6.5 & CUDA 7.0
  Silenced warnings concerning Thrust OMP backend

#######################################
#            Cusp v0.4.0              #
#######################################

Summary
  Cusp v0.4.0 provides support for CUDA 5.5 and Thrust v1.7.  Version
  0.4.0 includes several new graph algorithms based on backend integration
  with back40computing, a refactored smoothed aggregation solver allowing
  user-defined functions for core components and experimental work concerning
  sparse matrix visualization.

New Features
  array2d formats allow access to row and column elements regardless of orientation
  gallery method to generate grids
  OpenGL implementation of spy to view sparse matrices
  Generalized multilevel class
  Added Sparse * Dense multiplication routine

  Algorithms
     cusp::graph::bfs
     cusp::graph::connected_components
     cusp::graph::hilbert_curve
     cusp::graph::maximum_flow
     cusp::graph::max_flow_to_min_cut
     cusp::graph::pseudo_peripheral_vertex
     cusp::graph::symmetric_rcm
     cusp::krylov::cr

Bug Fixes
  Resolved issues related to Thrust 1.6 & Thrust 1.7
  Resolved issues related to CUDA 5.5
  Silenced warnings concerning uninitialized memory in generalized SpMV

